WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.207
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:06.715 --> 00:09.878
<i>(narrator) YOU UNLOCK THIS DOOR
WITH THE KEY OF IMAGINATION.</i>

00:09.968 --> 00:11.879
<i>BEYOND IT IS
ANOTHER DIMENSION--</i>

00:11.970 --> 00:13.222
<i>A DIMENSION OF SOUND...</i>

00:13.305 --> 00:14.670
<i>[glass shattering]</i>

00:14.765 --> 00:16.676
<i>A DIMENSION OF SIGHT...</i>

00:16.767 --> 00:18.758
<i>A DIMENSION OF MIND.</i>

00:18.852 --> 00:22.061
<i>YOU'RE MOVING INTO A LAND
OF BOTH SHADOW AND SUBSTANCE,</i>

00:22.147 --> 00:24.013
<i>OF THINGS AND IDEAS.</i>

00:24.107 --> 00:26.849
<i>YOU'VE JUST CROSSED OVER
INTO THE TWILIGHT ZONE.</i>

00:41.375 --> 00:43.537
IS THIS THE BO
FROM HUONG HOA?

00:43.627 --> 00:44.913
THAT'S RIGHT, SIR.

00:45.003 --> 00:46.914
WE WERE CAUGHT
IN AN AMBUSH.

00:47.005 --> 00:49.542
"MULTIPLE SHRAPNEL, ABDOMEN.

00:49.633 --> 00:51.874
EXTENSIVE TISSUE DAMAGE."

00:51.969 --> 00:53.926
WELL, WE CAN'T
TOUCH HIM HERE.

00:54.012 --> 00:56.265
WE'LL HAVE TO SEND
HIM ON BACK.

00:56.348 --> 00:58.055
WHAT ARE
HIS CHANCES, SIR?

00:58.141 --> 01:01.759
NOT VERY GOOD,
I'M AFRAID.

01:01.853 --> 01:03.389
"PHILLIPS, PIP."

01:03.480 --> 01:08.270
"PIP." THAT'S AN ODD NAME.

01:08.360 --> 01:12.900
WELL, PRIVATE PIP,
I WISH YOU A LONG LIFE.

01:12.990 --> 01:14.901
OR, SHORT OF THAT,
SOMEONE TO MOURN.

01:18.912 --> 01:20.289
[groan]

01:20.372 --> 01:22.283
<i>[explosion, off]</i>

01:22.374 --> 01:23.455
NO, PLEASE!

02:09.045 --> 02:12.710
<i>(narrator) SUBMITTED FOR YOUR
APPROVAL, ONE MAX PHILLIPS,</i>

02:12.799 --> 02:15.507
<i>A SLIGHTLY THE-WORSE-FOR-WEAR
MAKER OF BOOK</i>

02:15.594 --> 02:18.677
<i>WHOSE LIFE HAS BEEN AS DRAB
AND UNDISTINGUISHED</i>

02:18.764 --> 02:20.550
<i>AS A BUNDLE OF DIRTY CLOTHES.</i>

02:20.641 --> 02:22.507
AND, THOUGH IT'S VERY LATE
IN HIS DAY,

02:22.601 --> 02:24.638
HE HAS AN ERRANT WISH
THAT THE REST OF HIS LIFE

02:24.728 --> 02:26.139
MIGHT BE SENT OUT
TO A LAUNDRY,

02:26.229 --> 02:28.482
TO COME BACK
SHINY AND CLEAN,

02:28.565 --> 02:31.774
THIS TO BE A GIFT OF LOVE
TO A SON NAMED PIP.

02:31.860 --> 02:34.477
MR. MAX PHILLIPS,
HOMO SAPIENS,

02:34.529 --> 02:38.488
VVHO IS SOON TO DISCOVER THAT MAN
IS NOT AS VVISE AS HE THINKS--

02:38.575 --> 02:41.158
SAID LESSON TO BE LEARNED
IN THE TWILIGHT ZONE.

02:59.471 --> 03:01.838
[knocking at door]

03:01.890 --> 03:03.176
YEAH.

03:06.687 --> 03:09.179
[sniffs] WHEW. IT SMELLS
LIKE A BREWERY IN HERE.

03:09.272 --> 03:10.353
NICE, HUH?

03:10.440 --> 03:11.430
NICE, NO.

03:11.525 --> 03:15.359
TYPICAL, YES.

03:15.445 --> 03:17.607
GOT A
VISITOR DOWNSTAIRS.

03:17.698 --> 03:19.314
SOME KID.

03:19.408 --> 03:21.365
DID I EVER TELL YOU
I LOVE YOU, MRS. FEENEY?

03:21.451 --> 03:23.909
OFTEN AND ENDLESSLY.

03:23.995 --> 03:25.406
WELL, I DO LOVE YOU.

03:25.497 --> 03:27.864
<i>YOU'RE THE
QUEEN OF WOMEN.</i>

03:27.958 --> 03:29.289
MAILMAN COME?

03:29.376 --> 03:31.287
COME AND GONE.

03:31.378 --> 03:33.460
ANYTHING FOR ME?

03:33.547 --> 03:35.288
NOPE.

03:35.382 --> 03:38.875
[softly] NOTHING...
FROM THE KID?

03:38.969 --> 03:41.677
NO. NOT THIS TIME.

03:41.763 --> 03:43.094
BUT DON'T
WORRY ABOUT HIM.

03:43.181 --> 03:46.890
HE'S ALL RIGHT.

03:46.977 --> 03:49.389
YOU AIN'T GONNA DO
YOURSELF ANY GOOD.

03:49.438 --> 03:50.974
YOU KNOW THAT.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.601
AN ASTUTE OBSERVATION,
MRS. FEENEY.

03:53.692 --> 03:57.185
OH, I LOVE YOU AND YOUR
ASTUTE OBSERVATIONS.

03:57.279 --> 03:58.269
I MEAN IT.

03:58.363 --> 03:59.478
I REALLY MEAN IT.

03:59.573 --> 04:02.656
I KNOW.

04:02.743 --> 04:04.859
HOW 'BOUT IT,
MRS. FEENEY?

04:04.953 --> 04:07.445
IT'S TO LAUGH,
ISN'T IT?

04:07.539 --> 04:09.121
ISN'T IT TO LAUGH?

04:24.765 --> 04:26.096
<i>[knock at door]</i>

04:26.183 --> 04:28.800
YEAH.

04:28.894 --> 04:30.430
HI, MR. PHILLIPS.

04:30.520 --> 04:35.230
COME ON IN.

04:35.317 --> 04:36.807
YOU WANT
A CIGARETTE?

04:36.902 --> 04:38.233
I GOT ONE.

04:38.320 --> 04:39.276
GOT TWO?

04:39.321 --> 04:41.437
YEAH!

04:41.531 --> 04:45.024
THANK YOU.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.530
UH... SHADY LANE
LOST YESTERDAY.

04:47.621 --> 04:49.953
THAT'S THE WAY OF
THE WORLD, GEORGY.

04:50.040 --> 04:52.782
THE RICH GET RICHER
AND THE LONG SHOTS LOSE.

04:52.876 --> 04:54.207
SO WHAT'S TO DO?

04:54.294 --> 04:55.830
YOU SAID HE HAD
A GOOD CHANCE.

04:55.921 --> 04:57.207
YOU TOLD ME HE RAN
GOOD ON A VVET TRACK.

04:57.297 --> 05:00.005
I SAID THAT?

05:00.091 --> 05:02.503
PROVING HOW LITTLE
I KNOW ABOUT HORSES, HUH?

05:02.594 --> 05:03.959
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

05:04.054 --> 05:05.419
I BET EVERY NICKEL
I HAD ON HIM.

05:05.514 --> 05:07.755
IT'S FUNNY, GEORGE.

05:07.849 --> 05:09.681
CAN'T THINK OF A THING.

05:09.768 --> 05:11.759
OH. BIG JOKE, HUH?

05:11.853 --> 05:14.015
LOTS OF LAUGHS.

05:14.105 --> 05:18.565
VVHERE'D YOU GET THE MONEY?
VVHERE'D IT COME FROM?

05:18.652 --> 05:19.562
I GOT IT.

05:19.653 --> 05:20.893
FROM WHERE?

05:20.987 --> 05:22.364
FROM... FROM
WHERE I WORK.

05:22.447 --> 05:23.687
"WHERE YOU WORK."

05:23.782 --> 05:25.193
A WHITE-COLLAR
HEIST, HUH?

05:25.283 --> 05:26.819
I BORROWED IT.

05:26.910 --> 05:28.696
YOU BORROWED IT,
SURE, YOU BORROWED IT.

05:28.787 --> 05:31.700
WITHOUT THEIR KNOWING,
YOU BORROWED IT.

05:31.790 --> 05:35.408
HOW RIGHT AM I?

05:35.502 --> 05:37.243
SO WHAT'S TO
DO, GEORGY?

05:37.337 --> 05:39.829
I'LL GO TO JAIL.

05:39.923 --> 05:42.335
I'LL MAKE BOOK ON THAT.

05:42.425 --> 05:45.258
POOR GEORGY PORGY,
ONE OF THE BREED--

05:45.345 --> 05:47.302
JOHNNY-COME-LATELY WISDOM

05:47.389 --> 05:50.051
GRAFTED ONTO A
SECOND-GUESSER HEAD.

05:50.141 --> 05:53.133
<i>SO I ASK AGAIN, GEORGY,</i>

05:53.228 --> 05:54.969
WHAT'S TO DO?

06:01.528 --> 06:04.816
<i>[knocking at door]</i>

06:04.906 --> 06:06.647
MAX PHILLIPS
IS OUTSIDE.

06:10.537 --> 06:12.824
I HAVEN'T SEEN
YOU IN FIVE DAYS.

06:12.914 --> 06:14.029
SEEMS LIKE YEARS.

06:14.124 --> 06:15.239
WHERE'S EVERYBODY?

06:15.333 --> 06:16.619
EVERYBODY'S GONE.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.246
WE SETTLED
ACCOUNTS TONIGHT.

06:18.336 --> 06:19.451
WHERE WERE YOU?

06:19.546 --> 06:20.707
A REASONABLE QUESTION.

06:20.797 --> 06:22.253
ITOOK
THE WRONG BUS?

06:22.340 --> 06:24.377
YOU GIVE ME THE
WRONG STORY NOW,

06:24.467 --> 06:26.458
YOU'LL WIND UP
UNDER THE WHEELS.

06:26.553 --> 06:29.545
1,341 BUCKS. HEY!
THINGS ARE LOOKING UP.

06:29.639 --> 06:32.427
IT DEPENDS ON VVHERE
YOU'RE DOING THE LOOKING.

06:32.517 --> 06:34.724
FROM WHERE I SIT,
I DON'T LIKE THE VIEW.

06:34.811 --> 06:36.393
I DON'T
UNDERSTAND YOU, MAXIE.

06:36.479 --> 06:38.186
I TREAT YOU LIKE
A FAVORITE UNCLE,

06:38.273 --> 06:39.559
AND YOU
DOUBLE-CROSS ME.

06:39.649 --> 06:41.560
EGAD, CAUGHT.
[gasp]

06:41.651 --> 06:43.642
KID BY THE NAME
OF GEORGE REYNOLD

06:43.737 --> 06:45.227
PLACED A BET WITH YOU--

06:45.322 --> 06:47.313
$300, AND THE HORSE
DOESN'T PLACE

06:47.407 --> 06:49.614
AND YET, THE DOUGH
NEVER GOT TO ME.

06:49.701 --> 06:50.657
WHY, MAXIE?

06:50.744 --> 06:52.485
I'LL BITE. WHY?

06:52.579 --> 06:54.490
BECAUSE YOU GAVE IT
BACK, THAT'S WHY.

06:54.581 --> 06:55.992
YOU WELSHED ON ME.

06:56.082 --> 06:57.493
AND I HAD TO GO OUT,
FIND THE KID

06:57.584 --> 06:58.995
AND GET MY
DOUGH BACK.

06:59.085 --> 07:00.826
I HAD TO ROUGH HIM
UP A LITTLE BIT

07:00.921 --> 07:03.003
'CAUSE HE WAS STUBBORN.
THAT WAS A LOT OF TROUBLE.

07:06.301 --> 07:08.542
FOR 300 LOUSY BUCKS.

07:08.637 --> 07:11.504
YEAH, AN AWFUL
LOT OF TROUBLE.

07:11.598 --> 07:13.589
<i>BUT YOU KNOW
HOW IT WOULD BE, MAXIE,</i>

07:13.642 --> 07:15.178
<i>IF I LET THIS ONE PASS.</i>

07:15.268 --> 07:17.475
<i>IT'D BE THE FIRST
OF A LONG LINE.</i>

07:17.562 --> 07:20.600
<i>INSIDE OF THREE MONTHS,
I WOULDN'T HAVE A SHIRT.</i>

07:20.649 --> 07:22.515
<i>KID MUST HAVE
BEEN PERSUASIVE.</i>

07:22.609 --> 07:24.020
ASK THE KID.

07:24.110 --> 07:25.521
HE'S BEEN ASKED.
LOOK AT HIS FACE.

07:25.612 --> 07:27.148
IF I DON'T GET
THAT DOUGH BACK,

07:27.238 --> 07:28.615
I'M GONNA GO TO JAIL.

07:28.698 --> 07:30.029
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND,
MR. MORAN?

07:30.116 --> 07:31.857
I'M GONNA GO TO JAIL.

07:31.952 --> 07:33.909
YOU'RE TEARING ME TO PIECES,
KID, RIGHT IN HERE.

07:33.995 --> 07:35.781
YOU KNOW WHAT'S THE
MATTER WITH YOU?

07:35.872 --> 07:37.533
YOU LISTEN TO GUYS
LIKE MAX PHILLIPS.

07:37.624 --> 07:39.285
THAT WAS MISTAKE ONE.

07:39.376 --> 07:41.162
PHILLIPS NEVER GAVE
ANYTHING AWAY IN HIS LIFE.

07:41.252 --> 07:42.504
HOW RIGHT AM I, MAXIE?

07:42.587 --> 07:43.964
VERY RIGHT.

07:44.047 --> 07:46.459
A HEEL WITH A
ROBIN HOOD COMPLEX,

07:46.549 --> 07:50.087
BUT THIN AND SHORT-LIVED,
GEORGY PORGY.

07:50.178 --> 07:51.964
REMEMBER THAT
THE NEXT TIME

07:52.055 --> 07:55.389
SOMEBODY TRIES TO HAND YOU
SOMETHING FOR NOTHING.

07:55.475 --> 07:56.886
CONSIDER THE SOURCE.

07:56.977 --> 08:00.641
[phone rings]

08:00.730 --> 08:01.515
YEAH.

08:01.606 --> 08:02.562
WHO?

08:02.649 --> 08:04.515
HE'S BUSY NOW.

08:04.609 --> 08:05.815
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

08:05.902 --> 08:07.267
IT'S YOU R LAN DLADY.

08:07.362 --> 08:09.353
SAYS THERE'S
A TELEGRAM FOR YOU.

08:09.447 --> 08:11.700
YEAH, MRS. FEENEY.

08:11.783 --> 08:14.525
OPEN IT UP.

08:14.619 --> 08:16.405
DEPARTMENT OF
THE ARMY?

08:16.496 --> 08:23.539
WELL, READ IT TO ME.

08:23.628 --> 08:26.416
NO...

08:26.506 --> 08:28.008
[weakly]
NO.

08:32.636 --> 08:35.549
NO, I'M ALL RIGHT,
MRS. FEENEY.

08:35.640 --> 08:38.678
THANK YOU.

08:38.768 --> 08:39.849
[weakly]
THANK YOU.

08:52.615 --> 08:54.481
<i>[carnival music outside]</i>

09:04.127 --> 09:08.041
PIP IS DYING.

09:08.131 --> 09:11.044
MY KID IS DYING IN A...

09:11.134 --> 09:15.048
A PLACE CALLED
SOUTH VIETNAM.

09:15.138 --> 09:19.052
THERE ISN'T EVEN SUPPOSED
TO BE A WAR GOING ON THERE,

09:19.142 --> 09:23.477
BUT MY SON IS DYING.

09:23.563 --> 09:25.850
IT'S TO LAUGH.

09:25.940 --> 09:29.558
I SWEAR, IT'S TO LAUGH.

09:29.652 --> 09:33.566
HEY, MAX, OH, HEY,
KID, I'M SORRY.

09:33.656 --> 09:35.488
MY KID USED TO LOVE
AMUSEMENT PARKS.

09:35.575 --> 09:39.489
I USED TO TAKE HIM
ON SATURDAY NIGHTS.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.820
IT AIN'T LIKE THE KID'S
DEAD ALREADY.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.076
WHAT I
MEAN IS THAT--

09:43.166 --> 09:45.282
WHEN I WASN'T TOO DRUNK,

09:45.376 --> 09:47.788
OR WHEN I WASN'T
OUT CONNING FOR YOU,

09:47.879 --> 09:53.295
I--USED TO TAKE HIM
TO THE AMUSEMENT PARK.

09:53.384 --> 09:56.843
YOU KNOVV SOMETHING, MORAN,
I THINK YOU'RE VVRONG.

09:56.930 --> 10:00.673
I HAVE GIVEN
SOMETHING AWAY.

10:00.767 --> 10:03.725
MY KID, PIP.

10:03.812 --> 10:05.519
THE GOOD PART OF ME.

10:05.605 --> 10:07.767
THE CLEAN PART.

10:07.857 --> 10:10.235
THE PARTI
WAS PROUD OF.

10:10.318 --> 10:11.683
GEORGY, YOU
PUT THIS BACK

10:11.778 --> 10:13.439
WHERE IT
CAME FROM.

10:13.530 --> 10:15.646
NOW, MAXIE, I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOUR KID, BUT...

10:15.740 --> 10:17.606
NO MORE! NO MORE!

10:17.659 --> 10:19.616
2O YEARS AGO, I SHOULD HA\/E
SPIT RIGHT IN YOUR EYE.

10:19.661 --> 10:21.402
2O YEARS AGO,
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN

10:21.496 --> 10:23.954
HOW LITTLE TIME A MAN
HAS TO RAISE A SON.

10:24.040 --> 10:26.122
A LITTLE BELATED
HONOR NOW, GEORGE.

10:26.209 --> 10:27.574
YOU GET OUT OF HERE.

10:27.669 --> 10:29.000
WALK AS FAST
AS YOU CAN.

10:29.087 --> 10:32.170
DON'T LOOK
BEHIND YOU.

10:32.257 --> 10:35.466
MORAN, IF YOUR BOY IS
REACHING FOR A CIGARETTE,

10:35.552 --> 10:37.168
YOU TELL HIM THE
SMOKE BOTHERS ME.

10:37.262 --> 10:38.798
AND IF HE'S REACHING
FOR ANYTHING ELSE,

10:38.888 --> 10:40.174
TELL HIM I'LL CUT
HIS HEART OUT

10:40.265 --> 10:41.551
BEFORE HE HALFWAY
REACHES IT,

10:41.641 --> 10:42.802
THEN I'LL GO
TO WORK ON YOU.

10:49.065 --> 10:50.806
GET OUT.
GET OUT!

10:50.900 --> 10:51.935
<i>MOVE!</i>

11:08.334 --> 11:09.870
[distant traffic]

11:25.643 --> 11:27.304
I WAS GONNA CHANGE.

11:29.564 --> 11:31.054
THAT'S A FACT,
PIP, I WAS--

11:32.692 --> 11:34.683
IWAS
GONNA CHANGE.

11:34.777 --> 11:41.023
I VVAS... I VVAS GONNA MEET YOU
VVHEN YOU GOT OFF THE BOAT.

11:41.117 --> 11:43.654
SO NOW THERE'S
NO MORE BETS,

11:43.745 --> 11:45.361
AND THERE'S
NO MORE BOTTLES...

11:49.334 --> 11:51.166
BUT, OH...

11:52.629 --> 11:55.166
THERE'S NO
MORE PIP EITHER.

12:00.845 --> 12:02.085
OH, GOD--

12:04.641 --> 12:06.302
IF I--

12:06.392 --> 12:11.228
IF I COULD JUST TALK
TO HIM, YOU SEE?

12:11.314 --> 12:16.775
IF I COULD JUST SEE HIM...

12:16.861 --> 12:21.856
IF I COULD JUST TELL HIM...

12:21.950 --> 12:23.440
<i>[explosions in distance]</i>

12:26.871 --> 12:28.782
ALL RIGHT, MY FRIENDS,
THAT'LL DO IT.

12:28.873 --> 12:30.830
LET'S SEE IF HE'LL
SURVIVE FOR AN HOUR.

12:30.917 --> 12:32.499
IF HE CAN HANG
ON FOR THAT LONG,

12:32.585 --> 12:34.997
I THINK HE'LL
HANG ON FOR GOOD.

12:35.088 --> 12:36.999
WELL, GOOD LUCK TO YOU...

12:37.090 --> 12:40.208
WHAT WAS HIS NAME? PIP?

12:40.301 --> 12:42.417
GOOD LUCK TO YOU, PIP.

13:39.694 --> 13:40.684
PIP?

13:40.778 --> 13:42.485
PIP.

13:46.492 --> 13:49.280
HEY, PIP.

13:49.370 --> 13:52.453
(Pip) HEY,POP, I'\/E
BEEN WAITING.

13:52.540 --> 13:53.575
HEY, PIP!

14:04.260 --> 14:07.002
HEY, PIP.

14:07.096 --> 14:08.803
PIP, MY BOY.

14:08.890 --> 14:11.678
HEY, POP, I'\/E BEEN
VVAITING FOR EVER SO LONG.

14:11.768 --> 14:14.681
HEY, PIP.

14:14.771 --> 14:16.182
[kissing]

14:18.816 --> 14:20.773
[shouts]
OH, PIP, HEY!

14:20.860 --> 14:23.352
PIP.

14:23.446 --> 14:25.357
VVAIT, YOU'RE 1O YEARS
OLD AGAIN, PIP.

14:25.448 --> 14:27.439
HOW COME YOU'RE
1O YEARS OLD AGAIN?

14:27.533 --> 14:29.115
THAT'S WHAT I AM, POP.

14:29.202 --> 14:31.614
I'M 1O YEARS OLD, AND
IT'S SATURDAY NIGHT.

14:31.704 --> 14:33.786
YOU SAID TO MEET YOU
ON THE MIDWAY,

14:33.873 --> 14:35.329
AND I'VE BEEN WAITING.

14:35.416 --> 14:38.033
I WAS AFRAID YOU
WEREN'T GONNA COME.

14:38.127 --> 14:39.379
BUT--BUT I
DON'T UNDERSTAND.

14:39.462 --> 14:40.827
I REALLY
DON'T UNDERSTAND.

14:40.922 --> 14:42.629
SOMETIMES YOU DON'T
SHOW UP, POP.

14:42.715 --> 14:45.332
SOMETIMES YOU'RE--WHEN
YOU'RE SICK OR SOMETHING.

14:45.426 --> 14:49.090
YOU REMEMBER VVHAT I USED TO SAY, PIP.
YOU REMEMBER?

14:49.180 --> 14:50.215
I REMEMBER.

14:50.306 --> 14:51.717
I USED TO SAY--

14:51.808 --> 14:54.391
"HEY, PIP, WHO'S
YOUR BEST BUDDY?"

14:54.477 --> 14:56.935
"HEY, POP,
YOU'RE MY BEST BUDDY."

15:05.196 --> 15:06.982
OH!

15:07.073 --> 15:08.814
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?
WHAT DO WE DO?

15:08.908 --> 15:11.570
HOVV ABOUT SOME RIDES, POP?
OR SOME COTTON CANDY?

15:11.661 --> 15:13.902
SURE. SOME RIDES AND
SOME COTTON CANDY.

15:13.996 --> 15:16.249
ANYTHING YOU WANT.
ANYTHING AT ALL.

15:16.332 --> 15:19.495
BUT, PIP--PIP, YOU'RE
1O YEARS OLD AGAIN.

15:19.585 --> 15:21.087
SEE, I DON'T
UNDERSTAND THAT.

15:21.129 --> 15:22.585
IT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY DIFFERENCE NOW.

15:22.672 --> 15:24.288
WE'RE HERE, AND
WE'RE TOGETHER,

15:24.382 --> 15:25.668
AND WE CAN GO
ON SOME RIDES.

15:25.758 --> 15:27.260
SURE WE CAN.

15:27.343 --> 15:29.380
SURE WE CAN, PIP.

15:40.440 --> 15:41.896
COME ON,
LET'S GO.

15:51.284 --> 15:52.365
HEY.

15:52.452 --> 15:54.238
COME ON, POP.

16:02.128 --> 16:03.289
WHOA!

16:03.379 --> 16:04.369
POP, HELP, HELP.

16:04.464 --> 16:05.454
AH.

16:12.805 --> 16:13.966
HOW ABOUT THIS?

16:14.056 --> 16:16.639
OOH, NEAT.

16:16.726 --> 16:18.967
<i>[yelling]</i>

16:19.061 --> 16:20.313
COME ON, DAD.

16:20.396 --> 16:22.137
[humming]

16:29.155 --> 16:31.396
[gunshots]

16:31.491 --> 16:34.324
WORK THE GUN,
NOT THE JAWS.

16:37.288 --> 16:40.497
[firing gunshots]

16:40.583 --> 16:41.664
YOU HIT A DUCK.

16:41.751 --> 16:42.832
PIP, YOU HIT A DUCK!

16:42.919 --> 16:45.160
YOU HIT IT.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.585
PIP.

